\par \pard\plain \qj\fi284 \f2\lang2057 
\par This activity constitute the first step in model building.
\par The user create or modify the model internal structure using elementary {\strike\ul modules}{\v\ul !}{\v PopupId(`gloshelp.hlp',`lgc_gl_module')} from the {\strike\ul process module library}{\v\ul !}{\v PopupId(`gloshelp.hlp',`lgc_gl_proc_library')}
, instantiating them in the model (instantiated modules are called {\strike\ul blocks}{\v\ul !}{\v PopupId(`gloshelp.hlp',`lgc_gl_block')}).
\par Linkage between LEGO blocks are made connecting blocks' variables using the Variable Editor. 
\par During topology activity the user can instantiate new blocks, connect variables, delete blocks or connections.
\par The build up of the topologic scheme can be performed according to two modalities: Symbolic diagram (with the help of graphics) and Only by list.
\par \pard \qj\fi284\ri-6 
