\par \pard\plain \qj\fi284 \f2\lang2057 
\par \pard \qj\fi284\ri-6 In this modality the user can use a schematic representation of the plant as a worksheet for the construction/modification of the model structure. The model
 can be divided in multiple pages. The single page represents part of the model in terms of constituting blocks (shown as icons); using arrows, graphics symbols and labels the user can enhance information provided by the diagram.
\par Operations on blocks (such as blocks delete, modify description) are enabled when icons are selected. Selection can be performed in a graphical way (on the diagram page; graphic selection) or by selection in the scrolled list of blocks constituting the mo
del (on topology editor page).
\par 
\par \pard \qj\fi284 Topology activity shows two windows; see {\strike topology editor}{\v\ul lgc_tp_topology_editor_ly} and {\strike diagram page's index}{\v\ul lgc_tp_model_diag_pg_ly}
 for their layout. Through the diagram page's index is possible to open another window, i.e. {\ul model diagram page}{\v\ul !}{\v PopupId(`gloshelp.hlp',`lgc_gl_}{\v\ul model_diag_pg}{\v ')}. 
\par \pard \qj\fi284\ri-6\tx-568 
\par Connection of variables is made by user selecting two blocks (icons in the diagram page or items in model blocks list on topology editor page) and then opening their {\strike variable editors}{\v lgc_tp_variable_editor}. 
\par 
\par Information on the page layout is available in:
