\par \pard\plain \qj\fi284 \f2\lang2057 
\par \pard \qj\fi284\ri-6\tx-568 Filters are a series of strings of max. 4 char. used for selectively visualize only a group of input (or output) variables using variable editor.
\par Filter editor is activated selecting main window's pulldown menu button Option | Define Filter.
\par The user can specify a filter name (that will be used as a label in variable editor Filter option menu) and specify up to 10 filter strings. 
\par During Variable Editor filtering, are displayed only variables' names whose first {\b n} characters are equal to the {\b n}
 characters of one of the filter strings (where n is filter string's length). If you select a filter in Variable Editor's option menu input and output variables lists are updated accordingly (only variables accepted by the filter are displayed).
\par From main window's pulldown menu selection Option | Default filter the user can select which filter, from existing ones, may be applied when variable editor is called.
