\par \pard\plain \qj\fi284 \f2\lang2057 
\par \pard \qj\fi284\ri-6\tx-568 In order to connect variables related to two blocks, two variable editor (one for each block) windows must be opened. Variable editor must be opened when the block of interest is selected.
\par 
\par Variable editor shows two lists displaying block's input and output variables. If variables are connected a lock icon is displayed near the variable name.
\par 
\par Internal variable editor option allows the user to examine the name of corresponding connected variables of the other block (View menu) displayed directly below each name of the connected variables of edited block.
\par An option menu is also available to filter variable lists (Filter option menu) accordingly with user defined filters.
\par 
